    'guida.f3.step3.h': 'Noesis Editor opens in a new tab',
    'guida.f3.step3.p': 'The Summernote editor opens with all inline images (base64) and content already loaded. You can immediately highlight, collect chunks, save snapshots and edit text — all in the same environment. The chapter is registered in <code>noesisLibraryDB</code>.',
    'guida.f4.label': 'Phase 4',
    'guida.f4.h2': '📸 Snapshot <em>versioning</em>',
    'guida.f4.p': 'One of the most powerful features of v810. The Snapshot system creates a permanent backup of your work in HTML format on the local filesystem.',
    'guida.f4.step1.h': 'Click Save (green button) in the Chapter toolbar',
    'guida.f4.step1.p': 'The green <strong>Save</strong> button in the lower Chapter toolbar opens a prompt showing the proposed filename.',
    'guida.f4.step2.h': 'Optional: add a label',
    'guida.f4.step2.p': 'The prompt lets you add a custom label to the filename. Examples: <em>"firstRead"</em>, <em>"afterChunks"</em>, <em>"finalVersion"</em>.',
    'guida.f4.step3.h': 'Two files are generated',
    'guida.f4.step3.p': 'Noesis produces two HTML files simultaneously: <strong>_clean</strong> (without highlight colours) and <strong>_annot</strong> (with all highlights). Both are downloaded and also saved in IndexedDB. A confirmation toast appears.',
    'guida.callout.snapshot': '<strong>Snapshot best practice</strong> — Save a snapshot <em>before</em> making major edits. This way you can always revert to a previous version. The library shows the complete version history for each chapter.',
    'guida.f5.label': 'Phase 5',
    'guida.f5.h2': '📦 <em>Chunk</em> Collections',
