    'guida.profile.student.btn': '🎓 Student — Study workflow',
    'guida.profile.student.body': '<ol style="padding-left:20px; line-height:2;"><li>Import the manual (.epub)</li><li>Navigate to the chapter to study (TOC sidebar)</li><li>Read + highlight: yellow = concepts, green = examples, pink = terms</li><li>Extract the chapter (current + sublevels)</li><li>Save snapshot <em>"Base reading"</em></li><li>Add important selections to the collection</li><li>Save snapshot <em>"After chunk collection"</em></li><li>Open Noesis Editor → structure with H1/H2 and lists using the Inspect Panel</li><li>Export to PDF for submission</li></ol>',
    'guida.profile.researcher.btn': '🔬 Researcher — Deep workflow',
    'guida.profile.researcher.body': '<ol style="padding-left:20px; line-height:2;"><li>Import the paper/monograph (.epub)</li><li>Enable browser translation if in a foreign language</li><li>Select charts and images → add to collection (base64)</li><li>Select relevant quotes → collection</li><li>Save snapshot <em>"First review"</em></li><li>Export collection as JSON (backup)</li><li>Continue analysis, add annotations → save snapshot <em>"Full annotations"</em></li><li>Extract a chapter → Noesis Editor opens with chunks in Inspect Panel → structure the report</li><li>Export to DOCX for collegial review</li></ol>',
    'guida.profile.blogger.btn': '📝 Blogger/Creator — Fast workflow',
    'guida.profile.blogger.body': '<ol style="padding-left:20px; line-height:2;"><li>Read the book with Noesis</li><li>Select passages for the review → collection</li><li>Extract relevant chapters</li><li>Save snapshot <em>"Collected material"</em></li><li>Extract the chapter → Noesis Editor opens directly</li><li>Write the review in the WYSIWYG editor</li><li>Copy HTML → paste into CMS</li></ol>',
    'guida.profile.multilingual.btn': '🌍 Multilingual reader — Language study',
    'guida.profile.multilingual.body': '<ol style="padding-left:20px; line-height:2;"><li>Import novel in target language</li><li>Enable browser translation for native language</li><li>Read with dual reference (original + translation)</li><li>Highlight new words (pink)</li><li>Extract the chapter → Save snapshot <em>"Session 1 vocabulary"</em></li><li>Add difficult sentences to collection</li><li>Export collection JSON → personal archive</li></ol>',

    // ════════════════════════════════════════
    // LIBRARY.HTML
    // ════════════════════════════════════════
    'library.meta.desc': 'Noesis Library: manage your EPUB library, browse the books-chapters-snapshots hierarchy and access Noesis Editor in standalone mode.',
    'library.hero.badge': 'Environment · Noesis Library',
    'library.hero.h1': 'Noesis Library — <em>your knowledge library</em>',
    'library.hero.p': 'The Noesis entry point. Manage your EPUB collection, browse the books → chapters → snapshots hierarchy, and access Noesis Editor directly from the library.',
    'library.overview.label': 'Overview',
    'library.overview.h2': 'A <em>hierarchical</em> archive',
    'library.overview.p': 'Noesis Library organises your knowledge on three levels: each <strong>book</strong> shows <strong>extracted chapters</strong>, and each chapter exposes its <strong>snapshots</strong> saved over time — all accessible with one click.',
    'library.card.books.h': 'Books',
    'library.card.books.p': 'Each imported EPUB appears with cover, title, author and number of extracted chapters. Click the cover to open the book in <strong>Noesis Reading</strong>.',
    'library.card.chapters.h': 'Extracted chapters',
    'library.card.chapters.p': 'Below each book appear the chapters you have extracted. Click on the chapter name to open the most recent snapshot directly in <strong>Noesis Editor</strong>.',
    'library.card.snapshots.h': 'Snapshots',
    'library.card.snapshots.p': 'Each chapter shows its snapshots with name, variant (annotated / clean / origin) and save date. Click on a specific snapshot to open that exact version in the editor.',
    'library.img.library': 'Noesis Library — books, extracted chapters and snapshots hierarchy',
    'library.img.library.caption': '📚 Noesis Library — book grid with extracted chapters hierarchy and version snapshots',
    'library.toolbar.label': 'Toolbar',
    'library.toolbar.h2': 'The <em>Library</em> button bar',
    'library.toolbar.p': 'The top-right toolbar collects all global library commands.',
    'library.img.toolbar': 'Library button bar',
    'library.img.toolbar.caption': 'Library button bar',
    'library.btn.addbook.h': 'ADD BOOK',
    'library.btn.addbook.p': 'Opens the browser file picker. Select one or more <code>.epub</code> files from your device. The book is saved in <code>noesisLibraryDB</code> (IndexedDB) and appears immediately in the grid.',
    'library.btn.import.h': 'Import Snapshots',
    'library.btn.import.p': 'Imports snapshot files previously saved to the filesystem (HTML files with Noesis meta tags). The system reads the embedded <code>chapterId</code> and book name and automatically updates the hierarchy.',
    'library.btn.editor.h': 'Open Editor',
    'library.btn.editor.p': 'Opens Noesis Editor in standalone mode, without a pre-loaded chapter. Ideal for creating documents from scratch or from a collection imported via JSON.',
    'library.btn.tools.h': 'Tools ▾',
    'library.btn.tools.p': 'Dropdown with additional tools: <strong>Pandoc Online</strong> (document conversions in-browser via pandoc.wasm) and <strong>PDF.js Viewer</strong> (high-quality PDF rendering).',
    'library.books.label': 'Book management',
    'library.books.h2': 'Managing <em>books</em>',
    'library.books.p': 'Each book card in the library offers contextual controls for managing the title and its related content.',
    'library.book.open.h': 'Open in Reader',
    'library.book.open.p': 'Click anywhere on the book cover to open it in Noesis Reading. The reader automatically restores the last saved state (position, theme, font size).',
    'library.book.delete.h': 'Delete book',
    'library.book.delete.p': 'The red ✕ button permanently removes the book from IndexedDB and all associated chapter metadata from noesisDB. The snapshot files on the filesystem are <strong>not</strong> deleted — they remain available for future reimport.',
    'library.book.mozilla.h': 'Firefox compatibility',
    'library.book.mozilla.p': 'On Firefox, the Library is fully functional. The only difference is that the Tools dropdown may not show the Pandoc Online tool. All other features — import, reader, editor, snapshots — work identically.',
    'library.img.mozilla': 'Library toolbar on Firefox',
    'library.img.mozilla.caption': '🦊 Library on Firefox — all features available, slight toolbar differences',
    'library.chapters.label': 'Chapters and snapshots',
    'library.chapters.h2': 'The <em>hierarchical</em> structure',
    'library.chapters.p': 'The hierarchical structure below each book card gives instant access to all extracted work.',
    'library.ch.variants.h': 'Snapshot variants',
    'library.ch.variants.p': 'Each saved snapshot generates two variants: <code>_annot</code> (with highlight colours preserved) and <code>_clean</code> (clean version without colour formatting, ideal for reading or export). The <code>_origin</code> is the snapshot automatically saved at extraction time.',
    'library.ch.click.h': 'Direct navigation',
    'library.ch.click.p': 'Click on the chapter name → opens the most recent snapshot. Click on a specific snapshot → opens that exact version in Noesis Editor. No intermediate dialogs.',
    'library.ch.delete.h': 'Delete snapshot',
    'library.ch.delete.p': 'Each snapshot row has a delete button. Removing a snapshot from the library only deletes the IndexedDB metadata record — the HTML file on the filesystem is not touched.',
    'library.btn.theme.h': 'Toggle Theme',
    'library.btn.theme.p': 'Switches between Library light and dark theme. The preference is saved in localStorage and restored on next launch.',
    'library.btn.help.h': 'Help Overlay',
    'library.btn.help.p': 'Opens a contextual help panel with the main instructions for using the Library. Also shown at first launch.',
    'library.tools.label': 'Tools',
    'library.tools.h2': 'Accessory <em>tools</em>',
    'library.tools.p': 'The <strong>Tools ▾</strong> dropdown in the toolbar collects the built-in support tools.',
    'library.tools.epub.h': 'noesis-epub-tools',
    'library.tools.epub.p': 'Direct access to internal helper tools: <strong>ePub Slimmer</strong> (single file compression), <strong>Multi ePub Slimmer</strong> (batch up to 10 files) and <strong>ePub Splitter</strong> (creates standalone EPUB from selected chapters). <a href="helpers.html" style="color:var(--violet);">Helper documentation →</a>',
    'library.tools.pandoc.h': 'Pandoc Online',
    'library.tools.pandoc.p': 'Opens Pandoc Online in a new tab — universal document converter. Useful for transforming files exported from Noesis Editor into other formats (LaTeX, RST, ODT, etc.).',
    'library.tools.pdfjs.h': 'Mozilla PDF Viewer',
    'library.tools.pdfjs.p': 'Opens Mozilla PDF.js in a new tab. View, search and print any PDF file with high-quality rendering, without leaving the Noesis ecosystem.',
    'library.tools.img': 'Noesis Library — Tools dropdown open with three options',
    'library.tools.img.caption': '🛠️ Tools dropdown — noesis-epub-tools, Pandoc Online, Mozilla PDF Viewer',
    'library.standalone.label': 'Noesis Editor',
    'library.standalone.h2': 'Open the editor in <em>standalone</em> mode',
    'library.standalone.p': 'You don\'t need to extract a chapter to use Noesis Editor. The <strong>Open Editor</strong> button in the toolbar launches the editor in standalone mode — an empty document ready for any content.',
    'library.standalone.mode.h': 'Standalone mode',
    'library.standalone.mode.p': 'Empty editor with the full toolbar. You can write, format, insert tables and images, and use Excalidraw exactly as in <em>chapter</em> mode.',
    'library.standalone.chunks.h': 'Import chunks from collection',
    'library.standalone.chunks.p': 'Even in standalone mode, the collection Inspect Panel is available. You can inject chunks collected during previous reading sessions into the current document.',
    'library.standalone.callout': '<strong>Editor always in a new tab</strong> — Noesis Editor always opens in a separate browser tab, whether from Library (standalone) or from Noesis Reading (chapter). You can have Library, Reading and Editor open simultaneously.',
    'library.standalone.link': 'Noesis Editor documentation →',

    // ════════════════════════════════════════
    // NAVIGATION.HTML — Reading
    // ════════════════════════════════════════
    'reading.meta.desc': 'Noesis Reading: read EPUBs, annotate with 3-colour highlighting, manage bookmarks, customise themes and typography, and extract chapters into Noesis Editor.',
    'reading.hero.badge': 'Environment · Noesis Reading',
    'reading.hero.h1': 'Noesis Reading — <em>read, annotate, extract</em>',
    'reading.hero.p': 'The EPUB reading environment with hierarchical TOC, 15 themes, 3-colour highlighting, bookmarks and direct chapter extraction into Noesis Editor.',
    'reading.toolbar.label': 'Toolbar',
    'reading.toolbar.h2': 'The <em>Reader</em> button bar',
    'reading.toolbar.p': 'The Noesis Reading toolbar collects all reading and annotation tools. It is always visible at the top of the screen.',
    'reading.img.buttons': 'Noesis Reading button bar',
    'reading.img.buttons.caption': '← Library · Sidebar · Bookmarks · Highlight (yellow) · Display · Scroll · % · Save State (orange) · Extract Chapter (green) · ?',
    'reading.btn.library.h': '← Library',
    'reading.btn.library.p': 'Returns to Noesis Library without losing the current book state. Position is restored on next opening via Save State.',
    'reading.btn.sidebar.h': 'Sidebar',
    'reading.btn.sidebar.p': 'Opens/closes the expandable hierarchical TOC. Supports up to 3 nesting levels. Click any entry to navigate directly to that section.',
    'reading.btn.bookmarks.h': 'Bookmarks',
    'reading.btn.bookmarks.p': 'Opens the bookmarks panel. Add a custom bookmark for the current position with title and date. Saved in <code>localStorage</code>.',
    'reading.btn.highlight.h': 'Highlight',
    'reading.btn.highlight.p': 'Dropdown with 3 colours: <strong>Yellow</strong> (general concepts), <strong>Green</strong> (examples/key points), <strong>Pink</strong> (terms/names). Also: remove all highlights. Highlights are CFI-based and survive page reload.',
    'reading.btn.display.h': 'Display Settings',
    'reading.btn.display.p': 'Unified accordion panel with: 15 reading themes in 5 groups, font size, line height, page width, font family, background and text colour pickers.',
    'reading.btn.scroll.h': 'Scroll mode',
    'reading.btn.scroll.p': 'Toggles between paginated and continuous scrolling mode. In paginated mode, use arrow keys or swipe to turn pages.',
    'reading.btn.percent.h': '% Progress',
    'reading.btn.percent.p': 'Shows current reading progress as a percentage. Click to jump to a specific percentage in the book.',
    'reading.btn.savestate.h': 'Save State',
    'reading.btn.savestate.p': 'Saves the current state: chapter position, all display settings (theme, font, size, colours). State is automatically restored when you reopen the book from the library.',
    'reading.btn.extract.h': 'Extract Chapter',
    'reading.btn.extract.p': 'Main extraction button. Dropdown with two options: current chapter only, or current + all sublevels. Opens Noesis Editor in a new tab with content already loaded.',
    'reading.modes.label': 'Reading Modes',
    'reading.modes.h2': 'Three ways to <em>read</em>',
    'reading.modes.p': 'Choose the mode that best suits your device and reading style. You can switch at any time with the Scroll button in the toolbar.',
    'reading.modes.single.h': 'Single Page',
    'reading.modes.single.p': 'One page at a time with side arrow navigation. Ideal for small screens, tablets and focused reading.',
    'reading.modes.double.h': 'Double Page',
    'reading.modes.double.p': 'Two side-by-side pages simulating an open book. Optimal for wide screens (>1024px). Activates automatically based on window width.',
    'reading.modes.scroll.h': 'Continuous Scroll',
    'reading.modes.scroll.p': 'Uninterrupted vertical flow. Ideal for immersive reading and fast scrolling. Arrow buttons are automatically hidden.',
    'reading.toc.label': 'Sidebar TOC',
    'reading.toc.h2': 'Hierarchical <em>index</em>',
    'reading.toc.p': 'The sidebar shows the book\'s Table of Contents as an expandable tree up to 3 levels deep.',
    'reading.toc.nav.h': 'Chapter navigation',
    'reading.toc.nav.p': 'Click any entry in the index to navigate directly to that chapter. Position updates in real time.',
    'reading.toc.expand.h': 'Expand / Collapse',
    'reading.toc.expand.p': '<strong>▸</strong> = expandable node, <strong>▾</strong> = expanded node, <strong>•</strong> = leaf (no sub-levels).',
    'reading.toc.depth.h': 'Hierarchy depth',
    'reading.toc.depth.p': 'Supports nested TOC structures up to 3 levels — chapters, sub-chapters and specific sections all navigable.',
    'reading.toc.empty.h': 'EPUB without TOC',
    'reading.toc.empty.p': 'If the sidebar is empty, the book has no defined index. You can still navigate with arrows or in continuous scroll.',
    'reading.nav.label': 'Navigation',
    'reading.nav.h2': '<em>Floating</em> navigation buttons',
    'reading.nav.left.h': 'Left Arrow',
    'reading.nav.left.p': 'Previous page or chapter. Hidden in scroll mode and at the first chapter of the book.',
    'reading.nav.right.h': 'Right Arrow',
    'reading.nav.right.p': 'Next page or chapter. Appears as a circular button on the right side of the screen.',
    'reading.nav.click.h': 'Side click',
    'reading.nav.click.p': 'In paginated mode: click on the left half to go back, click on the right half to go forward. Fast alternative to buttons.',
    'reading.display.label': 'Display Settings',
    'reading.display.h2': 'Typography, themes and interface <em>in one panel</em>',
    'reading.display.p': 'The <strong>Display</strong> button opens a unified accordion panel with all display controls: typography, reading themes and interface colours.',
    'reading.display.fontsize.h': 'Font Size',
    'reading.display.fontsize.p': '<strong>A−</strong> and <strong>A+</strong> buttons to reduce or increase text. Range: 50%–200% of the EPUB\'s base size.',
    'reading.display.lineheight.h': 'Line Height',
    'reading.display.lineheight.p': '<strong>≡−</strong> and <strong>≡+</strong> buttons for line spacing. Range: 1.0–1.8. Wider spacing improves readability on dense text.',
    'reading.display.single.h': 'Single Page',
    'reading.display.single.p': 'Forces single-column display regardless of screen width.',
    'reading.display.double.h': 'Double Page',
    'reading.display.double.p': 'Forces two-column side-by-side display simulating an open book.',
    'reading.display.img': 'Noesis Reading — dual page mode with Display panel open',
    'reading.display.img.caption': '👁 Display Settings — typography and page layout in the accordion panel',
    'reading.display.tip': '<strong>Per-book preferences</strong> — Typography settings are saved per book via the <strong>Save State</strong> button. Each EPUB remembers its own configuration.',
    'reading.themegroup.warm': 'Warm',
    'reading.themegroup.lightgray': 'Light Gray',
    'reading.themegroup.darkgray': 'Dark Gray',
    'reading.themegroup.night': 'Night',
    'reading.themes.callout': '<strong>True Black for OLED</strong> — The True Black theme uses absolute black background (#000000) — ideal for OLED/AMOLED screens because switched-off pixels consume no energy.',
    'reading.interface.label': 'Display Settings — Interface',
    'reading.interface.h2': '<em>Interface</em> settings',
    'reading.interface.p': 'The Interface section in the <strong>Display Settings</strong> panel customises the colours of all interface elements and their opacity.',
    'reading.interface.toolbar.h': 'Toolbar Color',
    'reading.interface.toolbar.p': 'Background colour of the main reader toolbar.',
    'reading.interface.sidebar.h': 'Sidebar Color',
    'reading.interface.sidebar.p': 'Background colour of the TOC sidebar. Can differ from the toolbar to visually distinguish the two areas.',
    'reading.interface.navbtn.h': 'Nav Buttons Color',
    'reading.interface.navbtn.p': 'Colour of the floating navigation buttons (◀ ▶).',
    'reading.interface.opacity.h': 'Nav Opacity',
    'reading.interface.opacity.p': 'Slider 0–100%: adjusts the opacity of the toolbar and controls. Reduce it for a more immersive experience.',
    'reading.hl.none.h': 'None / Remove',
    'reading.hl.none.p': 'Deactivates the active highlight. Select "None" and click on highlighted text to remove the colour.',
    'reading.highlight.callout': '<strong>Reader highlights stay in the reader</strong> — Noesis Editor has its own inline highlighting system based on Summernote. The two systems are independent and operate on their respective interfaces.',
    'reading.bookmark.create.h': 'Create a bookmark',
    'reading.bookmark.create.p': 'Click the <strong>🔖 Bookmarks</strong> button in the toolbar → the My Bookmarks panel opens → click <strong>New Bookmark</strong>. The bookmark saves the exact CFI position of the cursor in the text.',
    'reading.bookmark.panel.h': 'My Bookmarks panel',
    'reading.bookmark.panel.p': 'List of all bookmarks for the current book, ordered by creation date. Each entry shows title, surrounding text preview and date.',
    'reading.bookmark.goto.h': 'Go to a bookmark',
    'reading.bookmark.goto.p': 'Click any bookmark in the panel to navigate directly to that position in the text.',
    'reading.bookmark.del.h': 'Delete a bookmark',
    'reading.bookmark.del.p': 'Click the X next to the bookmark to remove it. Removal is immediate and updates the button badge.',
    'reading.savestate.label': 'Persistence',
    'reading.savestate.h2': 'Save State — <em>save everything</em>',
    'reading.savestate.p': 'The <strong>💾 Save State</strong> button manually saves the current reading position and all preferences associated with the specific book.',
    'reading.savestate.what.h': 'What is saved',
    'reading.savestate.what.p': 'Exact CFI position in the text, font size, line height, page mode (single/double), reading theme, interface colours and scroll mode.',
    'reading.savestate.perbook.h': 'Per book',
    'reading.savestate.perbook.p': 'Preferences are saved per book individually in <code>noesisLibraryDB</code>. Each EPUB remembers its own configuration independently from others.',
    'reading.savestate.callout': '<strong>Automatic restore</strong> — When you reopen a book from Noesis Library, position and preferences are automatically restored to the last saved state.',
    'reading.savestate.table.key': 'localStorage key',
    'reading.savestate.table.content': 'Content',
    'reading.savestate.table.scope': 'Scope',
    'reading.savestate.scope.global': 'Global',
    'reading.savestate.scope.perbook': 'Per book',
    'reading.extract.single.h': 'Current chapter only',
    'reading.extract.single.p': 'Extracts only the chapter currently shown in the reader. Focused document, ideal for annotating a single section.',
    'reading.extract.deep.h': 'Current + all sublevels',
    'reading.extract.deep.p': 'Extracts the current chapter plus all nested sub-chapters, assembled in EPUB spine order. Ideal for broad sections.',
    'reading.extract.callout': '<strong>Direct extraction</strong> — The chapter opens directly in Noesis Editor in a new tab. All images are converted to inline base64 — the document is completely self-contained.',
    'reading.extract.link': 'Noesis Editor documentation →',
    'reading.pagenav.prev': '← Noesis Library',
    'reading.pagenav.next': 'Noesis Editor →',
    'reading.img.toc': 'Noesis Reading TOC sidebar — hierarchical table of contents',
    'reading.img.toc.caption': '☰ Hierarchical TOC sidebar — expandable up to 3 levels with direct navigation',
    'reading.themes.label': 'Reading Themes',
    'reading.themes.h2': '15 themes in <em>5 groups</em>',
    'reading.themes.p': 'The Display Settings panel offers 15 predefined themes organised into 5 groups by luminosity. You can also customise background and text colours directly with the pickers.',
    'reading.themegroup.light': 'Light',
    'reading.themegroup.gray': 'Gray',
    'reading.themegroup.dark': 'Dark',
    'reading.img.themes': 'Reading theme selection — 15 themes in 5 groups',
    'reading.img.themes.caption': '🎨 Display panel — 15 themes in 5 groups, customisable typography',
    'reading.highlight.label': 'Highlighting',
    'reading.highlight.h2': '3-colour <em>annotation</em> system',
    'reading.highlight.p': 'Highlights are saved in <code>localStorage</code> using CFI (Canonical Fragment Identifiers) — a standardised system for referencing positions in EPUBs. They survive page reload and book reopening.',
    'reading.hl.yellow.h': 'Yellow — General concepts',
    'reading.hl.yellow.p': 'Ideal for key passages, main arguments, definitions.',
    'reading.hl.green.h': 'Green — Examples and key points',
    'reading.hl.green.p': 'For practical examples, important data, empirical evidence.',
    'reading.hl.pink.h': 'Pink — Terms and names',
    'reading.hl.pink.p': 'For technical terms, proper names, entities to remember.',
    'reading.img.highlight': 'Noesis Reader — active 3-colour highlighting on text',
    'reading.img.highlight.caption': '🎨 3-colour highlight system — yellow, green and pink with selective removal',
    'reading.bookmark.label': 'Bookmarks',
    'reading.bookmark.h2': 'Custom <em>bookmarks</em>',
    'reading.bookmark.p': 'The bookmarks system lets you save precise positions in any book with a custom name. Bookmarks are saved in <code>localStorage</code> and persist between sessions.',
    'reading.img.bookmark': 'Noesis Reader — custom bookmark panel',
    'reading.img.bookmark.caption': '🔖 Bookmark panel — add, navigate to and delete custom bookmarks',
    'reading.extract.label': 'Chapter Extraction',
    'reading.extract.h2': 'Two extraction <em>modes</em>',
    'reading.extract.p': 'The Extract Chapter button in the toolbar opens a dropdown with two options to match the chapter structure of your book.',
    'reading.img.extract': 'Extract Chapter menu — current chapter and current + sublevels',
    'reading.img.extract.caption': '📥 Extract Chapter — dropdown with the two extraction modes in the reader',
    'reading.storage.label': 'Local storage',
    'reading.storage.h2': 'Where <em>data</em> is saved',
    'reading.storage.p': 'Noesis Reading saves all data in local browser storage — nothing leaves your device.',

    // ════════════════════════════════════════
    // HTMLEDITOR.HTML — Editor
    // ════════════════════════════════════════
    'editor.meta.desc': 'Noesis Editor: EPUB chapter extraction, highlighting, snapshots and WYSIWYG Summernote in a single environment. Export PDF, DOCX, Markdown, HTML.',
    'editor.hero.badge': 'Environment · Noesis Editor',
    'editor.hero.h1': 'Noesis Editor — <em>extract, annotate and write</em>',
    'editor.hero.p': 'From the click on Extract Chapter in Noesis Reading, <strong>Noesis Summernote Editor</strong> opens directly: a single environment to read the extracted chapter, highlight, manage snapshots, collect chunks and build your document.',
    'editor.extract.label': 'Chapter Extraction',
    'editor.extract.h2': 'Two modes, <em>one click</em>',
    'editor.extract.p': 'The Extract Chapter button in the reader toolbar opens a dropdown with two options. Noesis reads the book TOC hierarchy and assembles the document automatically, which opens directly in Noesis Editor.',
    'editor.card.single.h': 'Current chapter only',
    'editor.card.single.p': 'Extracts only the chapter displayed in the reader. Focused document, ideal for quick reading, targeted translation or annotation of a single section.',
    'editor.card.branch.h': 'Current + all sublevels',
    'editor.card.branch.p': 'Extracts the current chapter plus <strong>all nested sub-chapters</strong>, assembled in EPUB spine order into a single document. Ideal for broad sections or entire parts of an essay.',
    'editor.img.extract': 'Extract Chapter dropdown',
    'editor.img.extract.caption': '📥 Extract Chapter — dropdown with the two extraction modes in the reader',
    'editor.how.label': 'How it works',
    'editor.how.h2': 'The extraction <em>process</em>',
    'editor.how.step1.h': 'TOC structure parsing',
    'editor.how.step1.p': 'Noesis reads the current TOC node and recursively identifies all child sub-nodes. For hierarchical extraction, the complete list of EPUB files to assemble is built.',
    'editor.how.step2.h': 'Image loading and conversion',
    'editor.how.step2.p': 'For each extracted chapter, Noesis accesses the image files inside the EPUB via JSZip, converts them to <strong>inline base64</strong> and embeds them directly in the document. The result is a fully self-contained HTML with no external dependencies.',
    'editor.how.step3.h': 'Payload generation and editor opening',
    'editor.how.step3.p': 'The HTML content is injected into a JSON payload along with <code>bookName</code>, <code>chapterId</code> and <code>chapter</code> mode. Noesis Editor opens in a new tab via Blob URL with content already loaded.',
    'editor.toolbar.label': 'Toolbar',
    'editor.toolbar.h2': 'The <em>Editor</em> button bar',
    'editor.toolbar.p': 'The Noesis Editor has a structured toolbar at the bottom of the screen, divided into three sections: Chapter, Collection and Tools.',
    'editor.img.toolbar': 'Noesis Editor main toolbar',
    'editor.img.toolbar.caption': 'CHAPTER: new · open · save snapshot · options | COLLECTION: add · export · import · options · preview · delete | TOOLS',
    'editor.chapter.label': 'Chapter section',
    'editor.chapter.h2': 'Chapter <em>management</em>',
    'editor.chapter.p': 'The Chapter section of the toolbar manages the current chapter — saving snapshots, opening new ones and configuring extraction options.',
    'editor.chapter.new.h': 'New',
    'editor.chapter.new.p': 'Resets the editor in place — empties the content area for a new document. Does not lose the current chapter in noesisDB.',
    'editor.chapter.open.h': 'Open',
    'editor.chapter.open.p': 'Opens a file picker to load an existing HTML file directly into the editor. Useful for reopening a snapshot saved on the filesystem.',
    'editor.chapter.save.h': 'Save Snapshot',
    'editor.chapter.save.p': 'The main snapshot operation. Generates two files simultaneously: <code>_clean.html</code> (no highlight colours) and <code>_annot.html</code> (with all highlights). Both are downloaded and also recorded in <code>noesisDB</code>.',
    'editor.img.snapshots': 'Noesis Editor — Import Snapshots panel with snapshot history',
    'editor.img.snapshots.caption': '📸 Import Snapshots — history of saved versions with load and delete options',
    'editor.excalidraw.label': 'Excalidraw',
    'editor.excalidraw.h2': 'Integrated <em>diagrams</em>',
    'editor.excalidraw.p': 'Noesis Editor integrates Excalidraw in a dedicated tab. Create diagrams, flowcharts and mind maps visually, then export them directly into your document.',
    'editor.img.excalidraw': 'Noesis Editor — Excalidraw integrated in dedicated tab',
    'editor.img.excalidraw.caption': '✏️ Excalidraw — diagram, flowchart and mind map creation integrated in Noesis Editor',
    'editor.collection.label': 'Collection',
    'editor.collection.h2': 'The <em>chunk</em> system',
    'editor.collection.p': 'The Collection section lets you collect content fragments — chunks — while working on the extracted chapter.',
    'editor.collection.add.h': '[+] Add chunk',
    'editor.collection.add.p': 'Adds a text chunk from the current selection, or activates capture mode for images (double-tap) and tables (long press).',
    'editor.collection.export.h': 'Export JSON',
    'editor.collection.export.p': 'Saves all collected chunks as a JSON file. Importable in future sessions to continue working on the same collection.',
    'editor.collection.import.h': 'Import JSON',
    'editor.collection.import.p': 'Loads a previously exported JSON collection. Chunks are added to the current session.',
    'editor.collection.preview.h': 'Preview',
    'editor.collection.preview.p': 'Opens the Collection Inspect panel: list of all chunks with visual preview, type (text/image/table), selection for export and delete button.',
    'editor.img.collection': 'Collection inspect panel with collected chunks',
    'editor.img.collection.caption': '📦 Collection Inspect — visual preview of text, image and table chunks',
    'editor.export.label': 'Export',
    'editor.export.h2': 'Export in <em>any format</em>',
    'editor.export.p': 'The export menu in the Noesis Editor Tools section offers multiple output formats for all use cases.',
    'editor.img.export': 'Noesis Editor export menu',
    'editor.img.export.caption': '📤 Export menu — all available formats',
    'editor.export.pdf.h': 'PDF (print)',
    'editor.export.pdf.p': 'Opens the browser native print dialog. For advanced rendering, use the PDF.js Viewer from the Library Tools toolbar.',
    'editor.export.docx.h': 'DOCX',
    'editor.export.docx.p': 'Word document generated by html-docx-js with full formatting. Compatible with LibreOffice, Google Docs and Microsoft Word.',
    'editor.export.md.h': 'Markdown',
    'editor.export.md.p': 'Markdown format converted by Turndown. Inline images are retained in the ZIP version.',
    'editor.export.html.h': 'HTML',
    'editor.export.html.p': 'Copies the complete HTML to clipboard for pasting into WordPress, Ghost or other CMSs.',
    'editor.summernote.label': 'Summernote Editor',
    'editor.summernote.h2': 'The <em>WYSIWYG</em> toolbar',
    'editor.summernote.p': 'Noesis Editor is built on Summernote Lite 0.9.1 + jQuery 3.7.1. The full toolbar offers all formatting controls, plus Noesis-specific extensions.',
    'editor.img.summernote': 'Summernote toolbar in Noesis Editor',
    'editor.img.summernote.caption': '✨ AI · B · I · U · S · X² · X₂ · eraser · font · size · colour · lists · align · indent · table · link · image · media · — · scissors · </> · ?',
    'editor.how.step4.h': 'Registration in noesisLibraryDB',
    'editor.how.step4.p': 'The chapter is registered as a <code>chapterRecord</code> in <code>noesisLibraryDB</code> (IndexedDB) with a unique <code>chapterId</code> and an empty <code>snapshots[]</code> array, ready for the versioning system.',
    'editor.unified.label': 'Noesis Editor Environment',
    'editor.unified.h2': 'One environment for <em>everything</em>',
    'editor.unified.p': 'Previously there were two separate environments: the "Extracted Chapter" and the "Report Editor". Today they are unified in <strong>Noesis Editor</strong> — a single Summernote editor managing reading, annotation, editing and export without intermediate steps.',
    'editor.unified.chapter.h': 'Chapter mode',
    'editor.unified.chapter.p': 'Opens with the extracted chapter content already loaded. Allows annotation with highlights, snapshot management, chunk collection and full text editing before export.',
    'editor.unified.standalone.h': 'Standalone mode',
    'editor.unified.standalone.p': 'Empty editor, accessible from the Library via the "Open Editor" button. Free use without a starting chapter — ideal for notes, drafts and independent documents.',
    'editor.unified.callout': '<strong>Opens in a new tab</strong> — Noesis Editor always opens in a separate browser tab via Blob URL. You can keep the library, reader and editor open simultaneously to switch between environments without losing work.',
    'editor.hl.label': 'Highlighting',
    'editor.hl.h2': '3-colour <em>annotation</em>',
    'editor.hl.p': 'Colour highlighting is available in Noesis Editor via native Summernote. Select the text and apply the background colour corresponding to the semantic category.',
    'editor.hl.yellow.h': 'Yellow',
    'editor.hl.yellow.p': 'Core concepts, definitions, key information to memorise. The primary colour of academic annotation.',
    'editor.hl.green.h': 'Green',
    'editor.hl.green.p': 'Examples, quotes, practical cases, empirical evidence. Distinguishes the concrete from the abstract in the text.',
    'editor.hl.pink.h': 'Pink',
    'editor.hl.pink.p': 'Technical terms, proper names, vocabulary to study. Perfect for language study and specialist nomenclature.',
    'editor.hl.remove.h': 'Remove highlight',
    'editor.hl.remove.p': 'Select the highlighted text and apply "no colour" to remove the highlight while keeping the text intact.',
    'editor.hl.callout': '<strong>Highlights are preserved in annotated snapshots</strong> — Save Snapshot saves two files: <code>_clean.html</code> (without highlights) and <code>_annot.html</code> (with highlights). You can return to any previous state of your study session. <a href="snapshot.html" style="color:var(--violet);">Snapshot documentation →</a>',
    'editor.chapter.options.h': 'CHAPTER — Options',
    'editor.chapter.options.p': 'Dropdown with additional options for the current chapter: rename, metadata information and other contextual actions.',
    'editor.collection.delete.h': 'COLLECTION — Delete',
    'editor.collection.delete.p': 'Deletes all chunks from the current collection after confirmation. The operation is irreversible.',
    'editor.toolbar.tools.h': 'TOOLS',
    'editor.toolbar.tools.p': 'Opens the tools panel with access to integrated helpers: Excalidraw, Pandoc Online and Mozilla PDF Viewer.',
    'editor.sn.ai.h': '✨ AI Assistant',
    'editor.sn.ai.p': 'First button in the toolbar. Opens the AI panel with summary, rephrasing and analysis functions for text selected in the editor.',
    'editor.sn.inline.h': 'Inline formatting',
    'editor.sn.inline.p': '<strong>Bold</strong>, <em>Italic</em>, <u>Underline</u>, <s>Strikethrough</s>. Applied with Summernote commands on the active selection in the WYSIWYG editor.',
    'editor.sn.script.h': 'Superscript and Subscript',
    'editor.sn.script.p': 'Superscript (X²) for mathematical notation, numeric citations and units. Subscript (X₂) for chemical formulas and scientific notation.',
    'editor.sn.eraser.h': 'Eraser — Remove formatting',
    'editor.sn.eraser.p': 'Removes all inline formatting from the selection: bold, italic, colours, font-size — restores pure plain text.',
    'editor.sn.lists.h': 'Lists',
    'editor.sn.lists.p': 'Bulleted and numbered lists managed by Summernote. Indentation is handled with Tab/Shift+Tab or the indent button in the toolbar.',
    'editor.sn.tables.h': 'Tables',
    'editor.sn.tables.p': 'Inserts a table with the grid picker. Once inserted, the floating contextual toolbar allows adding/deleting rows and columns without code.',
    'editor.sn.link.h': 'Link',
    'editor.sn.link.p': 'Inserts or edits a hyperlink on the selection. Opens a popup with the URL field and the option to open in a new tab.',
    'editor.sn.media.h': 'Media',
    'editor.sn.media.p': 'Inserts a video or audio element via embed URL. Useful for integrating multimedia content directly in the document.',
    'editor.img.editing': 'WYSIWYG editor with Summernote toolbar',
    'editor.img.editing.caption': '✏️ Noesis Editor — full Summernote toolbar with formatting and plugins',
    'editor.table.label': 'Tables Plugin',
    'editor.table.h2': 'Table management <em>without code</em>',
    'editor.table.p': 'The tables plugin adds a floating contextual toolbar that appears automatically when the cursor is in a cell. All structure operations are available with one click.',
    'editor.table.rowabove.h': 'Insert row above',
    'editor.table.rowabove.p': 'Inserts a new empty row immediately above the row where the cursor is.',
    'editor.table.rowbelow.h': 'Insert row below',
    'editor.table.rowbelow.p': 'Inserts a new empty row immediately below the current row.',
    'editor.table.colleft.h': 'Insert column left',
    'editor.table.colleft.p': 'Adds a new empty column to the left of the current column.',
    'editor.table.colright.h': 'Insert column right',
    'editor.table.colright.p': 'Adds a new empty column to the right of the current column.',
    'editor.table.delrow.h': 'Delete row',
    'editor.table.delrow.p': 'Completely removes the row where the cursor is with all its contents.',
    'editor.table.delcol.h': 'Delete column',
    'editor.table.delcol.p': 'Completely removes the current column with all its contents.',
    'editor.img.table': 'Table Editor plugin with floating toolbar',
    'editor.img.table.caption': '⊞ Table Editor — floating contextual toolbar with structure operations',
    'editor.imgplugin.label': 'Image Plugin',
    'editor.imgplugin.h2': 'Visual <em>resizing</em>',
    'editor.imgplugin.p': 'The Image Resizer plugin allows resizing images directly in the editor by dragging handles, without needing to enter dimensions manually.',
    'editor.imgplugin.select.h': 'Visual selection',
    'editor.imgplugin.select.p': 'Clicking on an image in the document shows a selection overlay with handles at the corners and centre sides — exactly like in graphics software.',
    'editor.imgplugin.resize.h': 'Drag resizing',
    'editor.imgplugin.resize.p': 'Drag the handles to scale the image. The plugin updates the element\'s <code>width</code> and <code>height</code> in real time during dragging.',
    'editor.imgplugin.img': 'Image Resizer plugin with resize handles',
    'editor.imgplugin.img.caption': '↔️ Image Resizer — selection and visual resize handles',
    'editor.imgplugin.callout': '<strong>Images always base64</strong> — All images in the editor are saved as inline base64: both those from the extracted EPUB and those imported from local files. The exported document is always self-contained and portable.',
    'editor.excalidraw.fork.h': 'Local Noesis fork',
    'editor.excalidraw.fork.p': 'Excalidraw is included as an integrated fork in the application — no external CDN, no data upload. It opens in a separate browser tab and works completely offline.',
    'editor.excalidraw.export.h': 'SVG and PNG',
    'editor.excalidraw.export.p': 'Export your diagrams as SVG (vector, infinitely scalable) or PNG (raster for immediate embedding). Then insert the file into the document via the editor\'s image plugin.',
    'editor.excalidraw.create.h': 'What you can create',
    'editor.excalidraw.create.p': 'Conceptual flowcharts, mind maps, cause-effect diagrams, relationship schemas, visual timelines. Any visual structure to support your study notes.',
    'editor.excalidraw.privacy.h': 'No data shared',
    'editor.excalidraw.privacy.p': 'The Noesis fork of Excalidraw sends nothing to external servers. Your diagrams remain local until you manually export them as files.',
    'editor.export.txt.h': 'TXT',
    'editor.export.txt.p': 'Plain text without formatting. Ideal for analysis pipelines, LLM model input, or lightweight archiving of textual content.',
    'editor.export.mdzip.h': 'Markdown + ZIP',
    'editor.export.mdzip.p': 'Markdown with images extracted as separate files and packaged in a ZIP. Ideal for documents with many base64 images to publish on platforms that accept asset uploads.',
    'editor.export.json.h': 'JSON',
    'editor.export.json.p': 'Complete document data structure in JSON format. Useful for programmatic integrations, structured backups or import into other systems.',
    'editor.export.callout': '<strong>Collection export</strong> — The export menu also includes options to export the current collection: JSON, HTML, MD and MD+ZIP. These options work on the collected chunks, not the editor text. <a href="collezioni.html" style="color:var(--violet);">Collections documentation →</a>',
    'editor.quickexport.label': 'Quick Export',
    'editor.quickexport.h2': 'Export the chapter <em>directly</em>',
    'editor.quickexport.p': 'In addition to the full export menu, Noesis Editor offers quick export buttons in the toolbar to export the extracted chapter content without going through the editor.',
    'editor.quickexport.pdf.h': 'Print / Save PDF',
    'editor.quickexport.pdf.p': 'Native browser print with optimised <code>@media print</code> CSS — hides toolbar, handles page breaks, preserves colours. Save as PDF from the browser dialog.',
    'editor.quickexport.docx.h': 'Save as DOCX',
    'editor.quickexport.docx.p': 'Exports the chapter in Word format with automatic download. The DOCX file is compatible with Microsoft Word, Google Docs and LibreOffice.',
    'editor.quickexport.pdfviewer.h': 'PDF Viewer',
    'editor.quickexport.pdfviewer.p': 'Opens Mozilla PDF.js in a new tab with the chapter content — high-quality rendering, zoom, text search and direct printing from the viewer.',
    'editor.quickexport.callout': '<strong>Images always visible</strong> — All images are saved as inline base64 in the extracted document. Exported PDFs and DOCXs are completely standalone — no external path to maintain, no broken images.',
    'editor.chunks.label': 'Chunk Collection',
    'editor.chunks.h2': 'Collect, inspect and <em>inject chunks</em>',
    'editor.chunks.p': 'During reading in Noesis Reading you can collect text chunks — paragraphs, quotes, extracts — into the collection. In Noesis Editor the Inspect Panel lets you view the collected chunks and inject them into the current document with one click.',
    'editor.chunks.inspect.h': 'Inspect Panel',
    'editor.chunks.inspect.p': 'The editor\'s side panel shows all chunks in the current collection with title, text and origin. Available in both <em>chapter</em> and <em>standalone</em> mode.',
    'editor.chunks.inject.h': 'Inject into document',
    'editor.chunks.inject.p': 'Click on a chunk to insert it at the current insertion point in the document. The text is pasted as formatted HTML, preserving the structure of the original paragraph.',
    'editor.img.chunks': 'Inspect Panel of the collection in Noesis Editor',
    'editor.img.chunks.caption': '📌 Inspect Panel — chunks collected during reading, ready for injection into the document',
    'editor.chunks.callout': '<strong>Chunks and collections</strong> — Chunks are saved in <code>noesisCollectionDB</code> (IndexedDB) per book. You can collect across multiple reading sessions and always find them available in the Inspect Panel. <a href="collezioni.html" style="color:var(--violet);">Collections documentation →</a>',
    'editor.importsnap.label': 'Import Snapshot',
    'editor.importsnap.h2': 'Reload a <em>previous version</em>',
    'editor.importsnap.p': 'Noesis Editor allows importing snapshots previously saved to the filesystem — even from different sessions or other devices. The system reads the Noesis meta tags embedded in the file and restores the correct context.',
    'editor.importsnap.file.h': 'Import from file',
    'editor.importsnap.file.p': 'Use the <strong>Import Snapshot</strong> button in the editor toolbar to open the file picker. Select a previously saved <code>_annot.html</code> or <code>_clean.html</code> file.',
    'editor.importsnap.meta.h': 'Noesis meta tags',
    'editor.importsnap.meta.p': 'Every snapshot contains meta tags with <code>chapterId</code>, book name and variant. The system reads them automatically and reconnects the document to the correct Library hierarchy.',
    'editor.img.importsnap': 'Import Snapshot in Noesis Editor',
    'editor.img.importsnap.caption': '📂 Import Snapshot — loading previous versions with automatic reconnection to the chapter',
    'editor.pagenav.prev': '← Noesis Reading',
    'editor.pagenav.next': 'Snapshot →',

    // ════════════════════════════════════════
    // SNAPSHOT.HTML
    // ════════════════════════════════════════
    'snapshot.meta.desc': 'The Noesis v810 snapshot versioning system — save, reload and delete versions of the extracted chapter.',
    'snapshot.hero.badge': 'v810 · Snapshot System',
    'snapshot.hero.h1': 'Versioning your <em>study work</em>',
    'snapshot.hero.p': 'Save the state of the extracted chapter at any time. Reload any previous version with one click. HTML files on local filesystem, no cloud.',
    'snapshot.intro.label': "What it is",
    'snapshot.intro.h2': '<em>Local</em> versioning for your notes',
    'snapshot.intro.p': 'The problem: when working on an extracted chapter — adding highlights, notes and chunks — you cannot revert to a previous version. A wrong action is irreversible. The Snapshot system solves this.',
    'snapshot.callout.new': '<strong>v810 — Filesystem Snapshots</strong>No EPUB reader or offline study tool offers persistent versioning of annotation work directly integrated into the reading flow, without cloud and without account.',
    'snapshot.flow.extract.h': 'Extract chapter',
    'snapshot.flow.extract.p': 'Chapter opens in a new tab with a unique ID',
    'snapshot.flow.study.h': 'Study',
    'snapshot.flow.study.p': 'Highlights, annotations, collect chunks',
    'snapshot.flow.save.h': 'Save snapshot',
    'snapshot.flow.save.p': 'Frozen version with description',
    'snapshot.save.label': 'Save a snapshot',
    'snapshot.save.h2': 'Photograph your <em>work</em>',
    'snapshot.save.p': 'Snapshots are created directly from Noesis Editor, not from the Library. When working on an extracted chapter, you can save a version at any time with one click.',
    'snapshot.save.step1.h': 'Open the chapter in the Editor',
    'snapshot.save.step1.p': 'From the Library, click on the chapter name (opens the latest snapshot) or on a specific snapshot. The Editor opens in a new tab.',
    'snapshot.save.step2.h': 'Click the Save button in the Chapter toolbar',
    'snapshot.save.step2.p': 'The green <strong>Save</strong> button (<code>bi-file-earmark-arrow-down</code>) in the lower Chapter toolbar section. A prompt shows the proposed filename.',
    'snapshot.save.step3.h': 'Optional: add a label',
    'snapshot.save.step3.p': 'The prompt lets you add a custom label to the filename. Examples: <em>"firstRead"</em>, <em>"afterChunks"</em>, <em>"finalVersion"</em>. Leave empty to use timestamp only.',
    'snapshot.save.step4.h': 'Confirm to save',
    'snapshot.save.step4.p': 'Noesis produces <strong>two HTML files</strong> simultaneously: <em>clean</em> version (without highlight colours) and <em>annotated</em> version (with all colours). Both are downloaded and also saved in IndexedDB. A confirmation toast appears.',
    'snapshot.callout.backup': '<strong>Double backup</strong> — Each snapshot is saved both as an HTML file in the Download folder (portable, archivable to cloud) and in IndexedDB (immediate access from the Library). If you clear browser data, you can reimport the HTML files via <strong>Import Snapshots</strong> in the Library.',
    'snapshot.history.label': 'History management',
    'snapshot.history.h2': 'The <em>Snapshot History</em> panel',
    'snapshot.history.p': 'The Snapshot History panel in Noesis Editor shows all saved versions for the current chapter, in reverse chronological order.',
    'snapshot.history.load.h': 'Load a snapshot',
    'snapshot.history.load.p': 'Click <strong>Load</strong> next to a snapshot to restore that version in the editor. The current content is replaced. <strong>Save a snapshot before loading</strong> if you want to keep the current version.',
    'snapshot.history.delete.h': 'Delete a snapshot',
    'snapshot.history.delete.p': 'Click the red delete button to remove a snapshot from IndexedDB. The HTML file on the filesystem is <strong>not</strong> deleted — it remains available for future reimport.',
    'snapshot.import.label': 'Reimport from filesystem',
    'snapshot.import.h2': 'Import <em>Snapshots</em>',
    'snapshot.import.p': 'If you have cleared IndexedDB data or are working from a different device, you can reimport snapshot HTML files directly from the filesystem.',
    'snapshot.import.step1.h': 'Click Import Snapshots in the Library',
    'snapshot.import.step1.p': 'In the Noesis Library toolbar, click <strong>Import Snapshots</strong>. A file picker opens accepting multiple HTML files simultaneously.',
    'snapshot.import.step2.h': 'Select the snapshot HTML files',
    'snapshot.import.step2.p': 'Select the HTML files previously downloaded. Noesis reads the embedded meta tags (<code>noesis-chapter-id</code>, <code>noesis-book-name</code>) to correctly identify the book and chapter.',
    'snapshot.import.step3.h': 'The library updates automatically',
    'snapshot.import.step3.p': 'Each reimported snapshot appears under the corresponding book and chapter in the hierarchical library. Immediately accessible with one click.',
    'snapshot.schema.label': 'Technical schema',
    'snapshot.schema.h2': 'The <em>noesisDB</em> structure',
    'snapshot.schema.p': 'The noesisDB database (IndexedDB) stores only lightweight metadata — the HTML content of snapshots lives on the filesystem.',
    'snapshot.img.library': 'Hierarchical Library with extracted chapters and snapshots',
    'snapshot.img.library.caption': '📚 Library — extracted chapters with their snapshots in chronological order',
    'snapshot.img.import': 'Import Snapshots dialog — file selection from disk',
    'snapshot.img.import.caption': '⬆️ Import Snapshots — select the snapshot HTML files to reimport to the Library',
    'snapshot.history.h2': 'Manage the <em>history</em> from the Library',
    'snapshot.history.p': 'Snapshot history is managed from the Library, not the Editor. Each extracted chapter shows the list of saved snapshots. From here you can load or delete any version.',
    'snapshot.history.callout': '<strong>Load overwrites the current content</strong> — Restoring a snapshot completely replaces the visible text in the chapter. If you have unsaved changes, save a snapshot before loading.',
    'snapshot.access.label': 'Hierarchical Library',
    'snapshot.access.h2': 'Access snapshots <em>from the library</em>',
    'snapshot.access.p': 'The hierarchical library (v810) shows all extracted chapters with their snapshots. From here you can <strong>open</strong> any version in the Editor, but snapshots are created from the Editor (see previous section). The Library is used to navigate and manage saved versions.',
    'snapshot.access.cover.h': 'Click on the cover',
    'snapshot.access.cover.p': 'Opens the book in the reader. Navigate normally and extract new chapters.',
    'snapshot.access.chapter.h': 'Click on the chapter name',
    'snapshot.access.chapter.p': 'Opens Noesis Editor with the <strong>most recent</strong> snapshot. Quick access to the latest version of your work.',
    'snapshot.access.snapshot.h': 'Click on the snapshot name',
    'snapshot.access.snapshot.p': 'Opens Noesis Editor with that specific snapshot. Direct access to any historical version.',
    'snapshot.schema.files.h': 'Real HTML files',
    'snapshot.schema.files.p': 'Each snapshot is a standalone HTML file — visible in the filesystem, portable, archivable in Git or cloud storage of the user\'s choice.',
    'snapshot.schema.manual.h': 'Manual versioning',
    'snapshot.schema.manual.p': 'The user explicitly controls when to save. There is no auto-save for snapshots — only the work you choose to photograph is preserved.',
    'snapshot.schema.reimport.h': 'Reimportation',
    'snapshot.schema.reimport.p': 'Snapshot files can be reimported at any time via <strong>Import Snapshots</strong> in the Library — Noesis recognises them via <code>noesis-*</code> meta tags.',
    'snapshot.schema.cleanup.h': 'Filesystem cleanup',
    'snapshot.schema.cleanup.p': 'Manage snapshots like normal files: rename them, move them, archive old ones. No database to clear.',
    'snapshot.scenarios.label': 'Use cases',
    'snapshot.scenarios.h2': 'Three ways to use <em>snapshots</em>',
    'snapshot.scenarios.study.btn': '📚 Progressive study — successive versions',
    'snapshot.scenarios.study.body': '<p>Extract the chapter → save snapshot <em>"Original text"</em>.<br>First reading with yellow highlights → save snapshot <em>"First read"</em>.<br>Second reading with green and pink highlights → save snapshot <em>"Deep study"</em>.<br>Chunk collection for the report → save snapshot <em>"Chunks collected"</em>.<br>You now have 4 versions of the chapter, each with its precise study state.</p>',
    'snapshot.scenarios.research.btn': '🔬 Research — parallel variants',
    'snapshot.scenarios.research.body': '<p>Extract the chapter → save snapshot <em>"Base"</em>.<br>Annotate with the first interpretive hypothesis → save snapshot <em>"Hypothesis A"</em>.<br>Reload snapshot <em>"Base"</em> → annotate with the second hypothesis → save snapshot <em>"Hypothesis B"</em>.<br>You can maintain parallel versions of the same chapter with different interpretations.</p>',
    'snapshot.scenarios.backup.btn': '💼 Safety — backup before risky operations',
    'snapshot.scenarios.backup.body': '<p>Before any potentially destructive operation (reorganising chunks, deleting highlights, loading a new editor launch) → save a snapshot.<br>If the result is unsatisfactory → Load to return to the pre-operation version.<br>It is a manual <em>checkpoint</em> before each critical phase of your work.</p>',
    'snapshot.pagenav.prev': '← Noesis Editor',
    'snapshot.pagenav.next': 'Collections →',

    // ════════════════════════════════════════
    // COLLEZIONI.HTML — Collections
    // ════════════════════════════════════════
    'collections.meta.desc': 'Chunk collection system: text, images and tables. JSON import/export, inspection and chapter selection in Noesis.',
    'collections.hero.badge': 'User Manual · Collections',
    'collections.hero.h1': 'Collect <em>content</em>',
    'collections.hero.p': 'Chunk collection system for text, images and tables. Inspect, select, export as JSON and feed the editor with your study materials.',
    'collections.intro.label': 'Chunk system',
    'collections.intro.h2': "What a <em>collection</em> is",
    'collections.intro.p': 'A collection is a container of content fragments — called <strong>chunks</strong> — collected while working on a chapter in Noesis Editor. Each chunk can be selected text, an image or an HTML table.',
    'collections.callout.memory': '<strong>The collection is in-memory during the Editor session</strong>Chunks are kept in memory during the work session in the Editor. To preserve them between sessions or share them, use the <strong>Export JSON</strong> button in the Collection toolbar to save a JSON file.',
    'collections.card.text.h': 'Text chunks',
    'collections.card.text.p': 'Any text selection in the chapter in the Editor. Includes HTML formatting (bold, italic, links).',
    'collections.card.images.h': 'Image chunks',
    'collections.card.images.p': 'Images saved as inline base64. Perfect for charts, diagrams and figures to reuse in the editor without external dependencies.',
    'collections.card.tables.h': 'Table chunks',
    'collections.card.tables.p': 'HTML tables with structure faithfully preserved — rows, columns, cells and attributes. Ready to be edited in the WYSIWYG editor.',
    'collections.add.label': 'Collection',
    'collections.add.h2': 'How to add <em>chunks</em> in the Editor',
    'collections.add.p': 'Chunks are collected directly in the WYSIWYG Editor, using the Collection toolbar at the bottom of the window.',
    'collections.add.step1.h': 'Text — Select and click [+]',
    'collections.add.step1.p': 'Select the desired text in the editor with mouse or touch. Click the <strong>[+]</strong> button in the Collection section of the bottom toolbar. A toast confirms the addition.',
    'collections.add.step2.h': 'Images — Double tap or long press',
    'collections.add.step2.p': '<strong>Double-tap</strong> (desktop) or <strong>long press</strong> (600ms, Android) on an image in the editor. The image is added directly without the [+] button.',
    'collections.add.step3.h': 'Tables — Long press on the table',
    'collections.add.step3.p': '<strong>Long press</strong> (600ms) on a table cell. The entire table is added as a chunk.',
    'collections.img.collection': 'Noesis Editor — Collection inspect panel',
    'collections.img.collection.caption': '📦 Collection Inspect — list of collected chunks with preview and management options',
    'collections.inspect.label': 'Inspect panel',
    'collections.inspect.h2': 'View and manage <em>chunks</em>',
    'collections.inspect.p': 'The Collection Inspect panel opens in a floating non-modal overlay in the editor. Shows all collected chunks with visual preview.',
    'collections.inspect.preview.h': 'Visual preview',
    'collections.inspect.preview.p': 'Each chunk shows a preview of the content: truncated text for text chunks, thumbnail for images, first row for tables.',
    'collections.inspect.select.h': 'Selection for export',
    'collections.inspect.select.p': 'You can select/deselect individual chunks for export. Export JSON respects the current selection.',
    'collections.inspect.delete.h': 'Delete chunks',
    'collections.inspect.delete.p': 'Each chunk has a delete button. Removal is immediate and does not affect the editor content.',
    'collections.export.label': 'Import / Export',
    'collections.export.h2': 'Persistence between <em>sessions</em>',
    'collections.export.p': 'The JSON format is the bridge for transporting collections between sessions, devices or editors.',
    'collections.export.json.h': 'Export JSON',
    'collections.export.json.p': 'Saves all chunks (or only selected ones) in a JSON file. The format includes type (text/image/table), HTML content and collection metadata.',
    'collections.import.json.h': 'Import JSON',
    'collections.import.json.p': 'Loads a previously exported JSON file. Chunks are added to the current session. Compatible with all Noesis Editor versions from v700 onwards.',
    'collections.use.label': 'Practical use',
    'collections.use.h2': 'Build a document from <em>chunks</em>',
    'collections.use.p': 'The collection workflow allows you to assemble study material from multiple chapters into a single coherent document.',
    'collections.use.step1.h': 'Collect while reading',
    'collections.use.step1.p': 'As you work through extracted chapters, add the key passages, significant images and relevant tables to the collection.',
    'collections.use.step2.h': 'Export and reimport',
    'collections.use.step2.p': 'At the end of the session, export the JSON. Open Noesis Editor in standalone mode (Open Editor from the Library), import the JSON.',
    'collections.use.step3.h': 'Assemble and export',
    'collections.use.step3.p': 'Use the chunks as building blocks to assemble the final document. Export as PDF, DOCX or Markdown.',
    'collections.add.p': 'Chunks are collected directly in the WYSIWYG Editor, using the Collection toolbar at the bottom of the window.',
    'collections.add.badge.h': 'Counter badge',
    'collections.add.badge.p': 'The <strong>[+]</strong> button shows a red badge with the total number of chunks currently in the collection. Updates in real time with each operation.',
    'collections.add.clear.h': 'Clear collection',
    'collections.add.clear.p': 'Click the <strong>Clear</strong> button (🗑️ icon, red) in the Collection toolbar to empty the entire collection. A confirmation prompt appears.',
    'collections.img.editor': 'Noesis Editor with Collection toolbar',
    'collections.img.editor.caption': '✏️ Noesis Editor — Collection toolbar at the bottom: [+], Import, Export, Inspect, Clear',
    'collections.export.callout': '<strong>Recommended workflow with snapshots</strong> — Before clearing a collection, save a chapter snapshot. The snapshot preserves the document state (including highlights) while the JSON preserves the collected chunks. You get two complementary backups of your work.',
    'collections.use.link': 'Discover the WYSIWYG Editor →',
    'collections.pagenav.prev': '← Snapshot',
    'collections.pagenav.next': 'Helpers →',

    // ════════════════════════════════════════
    // HELPERS.HTML
    // ════════════════════════════════════════
    'helpers.meta.desc': 'ePub Slimmer, Multi ePub Slimmer, ePub Splitter and PDF.js Viewer — additional tools to manage your EPUBs in the browser.',
    'helpers.hero.badge': 'User Manual · Helper Tools',
    'helpers.hero.h1': '<em>Additional</em> tools',
    'helpers.hero.p': 'Four tools to manage your EPUBs: high-quality PDF Viewer, single and batch image compression, and splitter to extract chapters as separate files. All in the browser.',
    'helpers.pdfjs.label': 'Tool 1',
    'helpers.pdfjs.h2': 'Mozilla <em>PDF.js Viewer</em>',
    'helpers.pdfjs.p': 'High-quality rendering of extracted chapters via Mozilla\'s open-source PDF viewer. Integrated into the chapter export flow.',
    'helpers.pdfjs.view.h': '📖 Advanced viewing',
    'helpers.pdfjs.view.p': 'High-quality PDF rendering with support for embedded fonts, complex layouts and accurate colours — superior to the browser print dialog.',
    'helpers.pdfjs.zoom.h': '🔍 Zoom and navigation',
    'helpers.pdfjs.zoom.p': 'Zoom in and out with precise percentage, page navigation with direct number input, full-screen view.',
    'helpers.pdfjs.search.h': '🔎 Text search',
    'helpers.pdfjs.search.p': 'Full-text search in the PDF with highlighted results. Useful for quickly finding specific terms in long chapters.',
    'helpers.pdfjs.print.h': '🖨️ Direct printing',
    'helpers.pdfjs.print.p': 'Print the PDF directly from the viewer using browser native functionality, with print-optimised layout.',
    'helpers.img.mozilla': 'PDF.js Viewer with extracted chapter',
    'helpers.img.mozilla.caption': '📖 PDF.js Viewer — high-quality rendering of the extracted chapter',
    'helpers.slimmer.label': 'Tool 2',
    'helpers.slimmer.h2': '<em>ePub Slimmer</em>',
    'helpers.slimmer.p': 'Compresses images in an EPUB file to reduce size. Useful for EPUBs with many high-resolution images that slow down loading.',
    'helpers.slimmer.compress.h': '🖼️ Image compression',
    'helpers.slimmer.compress.p': 'Compresses all images in the EPUB to JPEG with configurable quality. Maintains aspect ratio and image structure.',
    'helpers.slimmer.quality.h': '⚙️ Configurable quality',
    'helpers.slimmer.quality.p': 'Adjust compression quality (0–100). Values between 60–80 offer a good balance between size and quality for most EPUBs.',
    'helpers.slimmer.nodrm.h': '🔒 No DRM',
    'helpers.slimmer.nodrm.p': 'Works only with DRM-free EPUBs. Protected files cannot be processed.',
    'helpers.multislimmer.label': 'Tool 3',
    'helpers.multislimmer.h2': '<em>Multi ePub Slimmer</em>',
    'helpers.multislimmer.p': 'Batch version of ePub Slimmer. Process multiple EPUB files simultaneously with the same compression settings.',
    'helpers.multislimmer.batch.h': '📚 Batch processing',
    'helpers.multislimmer.batch.p': 'Select multiple EPUBs at once. Each one is compressed independently and downloaded automatically.',
    'helpers.multislimmer.progress.h': '📊 Progress',
    'helpers.multislimmer.progress.p': 'Progress bar for each EPUB during processing. Processed files appear in the results list as they complete.',
    'helpers.splitter.label': 'Tool 4',
    'helpers.splitter.h2': '<em>ePub Splitter</em>',
    'helpers.splitter.p': 'Splits an EPUB into individual chapter files. Each chapter is saved as a separate EPUB — useful for reading tools that handle large EPUBs poorly.',
    'helpers.splitter.split.h': '✂️ Split by chapter',
    'helpers.splitter.split.p': 'Each item in the EPUB spine becomes a separate EPUB with correct metadata. Chapter names are taken from the TOC.',
    'helpers.splitter.download.h': '📦 ZIP download',
    'helpers.splitter.download.p': 'All split EPUBs are packaged in a single ZIP file for download. No intermediate steps.',
    'helpers.pdfjs.callout': '<strong>How to access the PDF Viewer</strong> — The PDF Viewer is activated from the <strong>👁 PDF Viewer</strong> button in the extracted chapter toolbar. It is not a separate page — it is integrated into the chapter export flow.',
    'helpers.pdfjs.meta.p': 'High-quality PDF rendering directly in the browser',
    'helpers.slimmer.meta.p': 'Image compression for a single EPUB file',
    'helpers.slimmer.link': 'Open tool →',
    'helpers.multislimmer.meta.p': 'Batch compression of up to 10 EPUB files',
    'helpers.multislimmer.link': 'Open tool →',
    'helpers.multislimmer.queue.h': '🔢 Queue with individual status',
    'helpers.multislimmer.queue.p': 'Each file shows its own status: <span class="badge badge-gray">pending</span> → <span class="badge badge-violet">processing</span> → <span class="badge badge-green">done</span> or <span class="badge badge-red">error</span>.',
    'helpers.multislimmer.error.h': '⚠️ Error handling',
    'helpers.multislimmer.error.p': 'If one file fails (corrupt EPUB, unsupported format) the others continue processing. Clear error messages for each problematic file.',
    'helpers.splitter.meta.p': 'Extract selected chapters as separate EPUB files',
    'helpers.splitter.link': 'Open tool →',
    'helpers.splitter.callout': '<strong>Difference from Extract Chapter</strong> — The Splitter produces standalone <code>.epub</code> files (importable in other readers). The Extract Chapter function in Noesis produces standalone HTML documents with the integrated Noesis toolbar. They are complementary tools with different purposes.',
    'helpers.pagenav.prev': '← Collections',
    'helpers.pagenav.next': 'FAQ →',

    // ════════════════════════════════════════
    // FAQ.HTML
    // ════════════════════════════════════════
    'faq.meta.desc': 'Frequently asked questions about Noesis: EPUB import, snapshots, collections, export, browser compatibility and troubleshooting.',
    'faq.hero.badge': 'Support · FAQ',
    'faq.hero.h1': 'Frequently Asked <em>Questions</em>',
    'faq.hero.p': 'Answers to the most common questions about Noesis — from installation to snapshots, from privacy to browser compatibility.',
    'faq.setup.label': 'First launch',
    'faq.setup.h2': 'Installation and <em>setup</em>',
    'faq.q.install': 'How do I install Noesis?',
    'faq.a.install.p1': 'There is nothing to install. Download <code>noesis810.zip</code> from the homepage, unzip it and double-click <code>noesis810.html</code>. The file opens in the browser and the app is ready.',
    'faq.a.install.p2': 'For the best experience (especially with EPUBs that have external resources) start a local server: <code>python -m http.server 8000</code> in the extracted folder, then open <code>http://localhost:8000/noesis810.html</code>.',
    'faq.q.browsers': 'Which browsers does Noesis support?',
    'faq.q.mobile': 'Does it work on mobile?',
    'faq.a.mobile': 'Yes, Noesis is responsive and works on modern mobile browsers. The interface adapts to small screens with a hamburger menu for navigation. However, Noesis is primarily optimised for desktop use — document production (editor, export, snapshot management) is more comfortable on a computer with keyboard and large screen.',
    'faq.q.internet': 'Does Noesis require an internet connection?',
    'faq.a.internet': 'Only for the first load (downloads CDN libraries: ePub.js, JSZip, Bootstrap Icons, jQuery, Summernote, Mozilla PDF.js). After the first launch, Noesis works completely offline. Browser translation requires an internet connection (the translation service belongs to the browser, not Noesis).',
    'faq.books.label': 'Books and library',
    'faq.books.h2': 'Import and <em>book management</em>',
    'faq.q.noload': "The book won't load — what do I do?",
    'faq.a.noload.1': '<strong>1. Verify the file is a valid EPUB</strong> and is not DRM-protected. Noesis does not support DRM files.',
    'faq.a.noload.2': '<strong>2. Use a local server.</strong> Open a shell in the Noesis folder and run <code>python -m http.server 8000</code>, then access <code>http://localhost:8000/noesis810.html</code>. Many EPUB loading issues are due to CORS restrictions with the <code>file://</code> protocol.',
    'faq.a.noload.3': '<strong>3. Check IndexedDB</strong> in DevTools → Application → Storage → IndexedDB → EpubLibraryDB → books to verify the book was saved.',
    'faq.q.howmany': 'How many books can I keep in the library?',
    'faq.a.howmany': 'Technically unlimited — the library is only constrained by available IndexedDB space in the browser. In practice, modern browsers grant 50–100MB of IndexedDB storage by default (expandable). An average EPUB is 2–5MB, an EPUB with many images can reach 50–100MB. Use ePub Slimmer for large EPUBs.',
    'faq.q.images': "Images in the book don't display",
    'faq.a.images': 'Some EPUBs use non-standard relative paths for images — this can cause issues with the <code>file://</code> protocol. Solutions:',
    'faq.a.images.li1': 'Use the local server (<code>python -m http.server 8000</code>)',
    'faq.a.images.li2': 'Extract the chapter: images are converted to inline base64 and are always visible in the extracted document',
    'faq.a.images.li3': 'Use ePub Slimmer which rewrites image paths',
    'faq.q.toc': 'The sidebar TOC is empty',
    'faq.a.toc': 'Some EPUBs do not include a navigation file (NCX or nav.xhtml). You can verify by opening the browser console and checking <code>book.navigation.toc</code>. If it is empty or undefined, the book has no TOC and you can only navigate with the arrows.',
    'faq.snapshot.label': 'Snapshots',
    'faq.snapshot.h2': 'Questions about <em>snapshots</em>',
    'faq.q.persist': 'Are snapshots retained after closing the browser?',
    'faq.a.persist': 'Yes. Snapshots are saved as <strong>HTML files on the local filesystem</strong> via the browser File System Access API. Metadata (name, date, file reference) is kept in <code>noesisDB</code> (IndexedDB). Files remain on disk until you explicitly delete them from the Snapshot History interface or from the filesystem.',
    'faq.q.size': 'How much space do snapshots take?',
    'faq.a.size': 'Each snapshot contains the complete HTML of the chapter (no diff, no compression). An average chapter with text and some base64 images takes between 500KB and 5MB per snapshot. If you have many snapshots on chapters with many images, check space in DevTools → Application → Storage. Delete obsolete snapshots from Snapshot History.',
    'faq.q.transfer': 'Can I access snapshots from another device?',
    'faq.a.transfer': 'Not automatically. Snapshots are HTML files on your local filesystem — there is no cloud or sync (by design — total privacy). To transfer work to another device: copy the snapshot files to the same folder on the new device, then import them from the Snapshot History interface. Also copy the EPUB file and the Noesis file.',
    'faq.q.undo': 'I loaded a snapshot by mistake — can I undo?',
    'faq.a.undo': 'If you had saved a snapshot of your current work before loading, you can simply reload that snapshot. If you had no snapshot of the current work, the restore is not undoable — the content has been replaced. <strong>Best practice: always save a snapshot before loading a previous version.</strong>',
    'faq.export.label': 'Export and Editor',
    'faq.export.h2': 'Export, PDF and <em>DOCX</em>',
    'faq.q.pdf': 'PDF export does not work or fails',
    'faq.a.pdf': 'In v810, PDF export uses the native browser print (<code>window.print()</code>) — no external libraries required and always works offline. If the print dialog does not open, verify that popups are not blocked. Alternatively, use the <strong>👁 PDF Viewer</strong> button to open Mozilla PDF.js and print from there. For DOCX, use the DOCX button in the extracted chapter toolbar.',
    'faq.q.pdfimages': 'Can I export images in the PDF?',
    'faq.a.pdfimages': 'Yes. Images in the extracted chapter are already converted to inline base64. They are automatically included in PDF and DOCX export without additional configuration. The exported document is completely self-contained.',
    'faq.q.cms': 'How do I copy the editor content to my CMS?',
    'faq.a.cms': 'Use the <strong>&lt;/&gt; Copy HTML</strong> button in the editor toolbar. It copies all document HTML to the clipboard. In WordPress, switch to HTML mode of the editor (HTML Code block or classic editor → text); in Ghost, use the HTML block; in Webflow, paste into a Rich Text or HTML Embed element.',
    'faq.q.docx': 'The DOCX file opens badly in Word',
    'faq.a.docx': 'The DOCX generated by Noesis follows the basic OOXML format. It works well in LibreOffice and Google Docs. In Word some complex formatting (nested tables, large base64 images) may be interpreted slightly differently. For optimal Word compatibility, use print → PDF as the final delivery format.',
    'faq.privacy.label': 'Privacy and storage',
    'faq.privacy.h2': 'Data and <em>privacy</em>',
    'faq.q.data': 'Where is my data saved?',
    'faq.a.data': 'All Noesis data is saved locally in your browser. No data leaves the device. The storage used:',
    'faq.q.clear': 'What happens if I clear browser data?',
    'faq.a.clear': 'Clearing browser data (Clear browsing data → Cookies and cached files → IndexedDB) removes books from the library, extracted chapter metadata and snapshot metadata from noesisDB. <strong>It does not delete snapshot HTML files</strong> that you have saved to the filesystem — those remain available for reimport. Books must be reimported from the original EPUB files.',
    'faq.q.gdpr': 'Is Noesis GDPR compliant?',
    'faq.a.gdpr': 'Yes, completely. Noesis implements privacy by design: zero data transmission to external servers, zero tracking, zero analytics. All data remains in your browser and on your device. There is nothing to declare or manage from a GDPR perspective because no personal data is collected or transmitted.',
    'faq.a.browsers': '<div class="table-wrap" style="margin:0;"><table><thead><tr><th>Browser</th><th>Min. version</th><th>Status</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Chrome</td><td>90+</td><td><span class="badge badge-green">✓ Full</span></td><td>Native integrated translation</td></tr><tr><td>Edge</td><td>90+</td><td><span class="badge badge-green">✓ Full</span></td><td>Chromium-based</td></tr><tr><td>Firefox</td><td>88+</td><td><span class="badge badge-green">✓ Full</span></td><td>All features</td></tr><tr><td>Opera</td><td>76+</td><td><span class="badge badge-green">✓ Full</span></td><td>Chromium-based</td></tr><tr><td>Safari</td><td>14+</td><td><span class="badge badge-gray">⚠ Partial</span></td><td>IndexedDB with storage limitations</td></tr></tbody></table></div>',
    'faq.tech.label': 'Technology',
    'faq.tech.h2': 'Browser <em>APIs used</em>',
    'faq.tech.idb.h': '💾 IndexedDB',
    'faq.tech.idb.p': 'Persistent storage for books (EpubLibraryDB) and extracted chapters + snapshots (noesisDB). Asynchronous, supports large binary files.',
    'faq.tech.clipboard.h': '📋 Clipboard API',
    'faq.tech.clipboard.p': 'Captures text selections for chunks and copies editor HTML to the clipboard for pasting into a CMS.',
    'faq.tech.canvas.h': '🖼️ Canvas API',
    'faq.tech.canvas.p': 'Used for image compression and conversion in ePub Slimmer and for editor image resizing. PDF export in v810 uses native browser printing, not Canvas.',
    'faq.tech.translation.h': '🌐 Translation API (browser)',
    'faq.tech.translation.p': 'Native integrated browser translation (Chrome, Edge, Firefox). This is not a Noesis API — it is a browser feature that Noesis does not control.',
    'faq.tech.print.h': '🖨️ Print API',
    'faq.tech.print.p': 'Native printing and PDF saving via <code>window.print()</code> with <code>@media print</code> CSS optimised for each context (reader, extracted chapter, editor).',
    'faq.tech.filereader.h': '📁 FileReader API',
    'faq.tech.filereader.p': 'Import of EPUB files and images from the user filesystem. Read as ArrayBuffer for JSZip and as base64 for editor images.',
    'faq.pagenav.prev': '← Helpers',
    'faq.pagenav.next': 'Notes →',

    // ════════════════════════════════════════
    // NOTE.HTML — Notes & Changelog
    // ════════════════════════════════════════
    'notes.meta.desc': 'Version changelog, known issues and usage tips for Noesis EPUB Reader.',
    'notes.hero.badge': 'Version notes',
    'notes.hero.h1': 'Changelog, <em>Limits</em> and Tips',
    'notes.hero.p': 'Version history, known issues and suggestions for getting the most out of Noesis.',
    'notes.changelog.label': 'Changelog',
    'notes.changelog.h2': 'Version <em>history</em>',
    'notes.v810.current': 'Current',
    'notes.v810.date': 'March 2026',
    'notes.v810.li1': 'Excalidraw integrated in the editor — diagrams, flowcharts and mind maps in a dedicated tab',
    'notes.v810.li2': 'SVG and PNG export from Excalidraw, saved locally in the browser',
    'notes.v810.li3': 'Extract Chapter — 2-option menu: "Current chapter only" and "Current + all sublevels"',
    'notes.v810.li4': 'Pandoc Online available in the Library Tools dropdown — in-browser document conversions via pandoc.wasm',
    'notes.v810.li5': 'Expanded Help Overlay — full Button Reference for Library, Reader and Editor',
    'notes.v810.ch1': 'Snapshots migrated to local filesystem — real HTML files downloaded to disk, no longer in IndexedDB',
    'notes.v810.ch2': 'noesisDB keeps only metadata (ID, name, timestamp) to populate the Library',
    'notes.v810.ch3': 'Import Snapshots — reimport HTML files from disk into noesisDB with one click',
    'notes.v703.date': 'March 2026',
    'notes.v703.li1': 'Snapshot system — save, load and delete versions of the extracted chapter',
    'notes.v703.li2': 'noesisDB (IndexedDB) — dedicated database for extracted chapters and snapshots',
    'notes.v703.li3': 'Dark hierarchical library — book → extracted chapters → snapshots view',
    'notes.v686.date': 'February 2026',
    'notes.v686.li1': 'Complete Summernote Lite editor (sn56.x) replaces previous Quill-based editor',
    'notes.v686.li2': 'Excalidraw tab in dedicated editor tab',
    'notes.v686.li3': 'Full chunk collection system: text, images, tables',
    'notes.v686.li4': 'Multi-format export: PDF, DOCX, MD, MD+ZIP, HTML, JSON, TXT',
    'notes.v652.date': 'January 2026',
    'notes.v652.li1': '3-colour highlighting with CFI persistence (yellow, green, pink)',
    'notes.v652.li2': 'Hierarchical chapter extraction — current chapter + all sublevels',
    'notes.v652.li3': 'Custom bookmarks with localStorage persistence',
    'notes.v652.li4': '15 reading themes in 5 groups',
    'notes.v646.date': 'December 2025',
    'notes.v646.li1': 'Initial version — basic EPUB reader with epub.js',
    'notes.v646.li2': 'IndexedDB library (EpubLibraryDB)',
    'notes.v646.li3': 'Basic reading toolbar with sidebar TOC',
    'notes.known.label': 'Known issues',
    'notes.known.h2': 'Limits and <em>workarounds</em>',
    'notes.issue1.h': 'Android: File System Access API',
    'notes.issue1.p': 'On some Android versions, the File System Access API for saving snapshots may ask for permission each time. This is a browser limitation, not a Noesis bug. Workaround: use the Desktop version for intensive snapshot work.',
    'notes.issue2.h': 'Safari: IndexedDB limitations',
    'notes.issue2.p': 'Safari imposes stricter storage limits for IndexedDB. Large EPUBs (>50MB) may fail to import. Workaround: use ePub Slimmer first to reduce size, or switch to Chrome/Firefox.',
    'notes.issue3.h': 'file:// protocol: CORS restrictions',
    'notes.issue3.p': "Opening Noesis directly with the <code>file://</code> protocol can cause CORS issues with some EPUBs. Workaround: use a local server (<code>python -m http.server 8000</code>).",
    'notes.issue4.h': 'DOCX and complex Word formatting',
    'notes.issue4.p': 'The DOCX generated by html-docx-js has basic OOXML formatting. Nested tables and very complex images may not render perfectly in Microsoft Word. Workaround: use PDF for delivery, DOCX for editing in LibreOffice/Google Docs.',
    'notes.tips.label': 'Pro tips',
    'notes.tips.h2': 'Get the most from <em>Noesis</em>',
    'notes.tip1.h': '💡 Workflow tip: snapshot before editing',
    'notes.tip1.p': 'Always save a snapshot before starting major editing or structural changes to a chapter. The 2-second investment protects against irreversible data loss.',
    'notes.tip2.h': '💡 Multilingual reading: highlights stay on the original',
    'notes.tip2.p': 'Activate browser translation before reading a foreign text. Highlights are applied on the original text (CFI-based) and remain stable even when switching between original and translated view.',
    'notes.tip3.h': '💡 Large EPUBs: slim before importing',
    'notes.tip3.p': 'If an EPUB has many high-resolution images (>20MB), use ePub Slimmer before importing. Significantly reduces loading time and space in IndexedDB.',
    'notes.tip4.h': '💡 Export for CMS: use Copy HTML',
    'notes.tip4.p': 'For WordPress, Ghost or Webflow, use the &lt;/&gt; Copy HTML button. The HTML is already clean with inline base64 images — paste directly into the CMS HTML block.',
    'notes.license.label': 'License',
    'notes.license.h2': 'MIT License — <em>free to use</em>',
    'notes.license.p': 'Noesis is open source software distributed under the MIT license.',
    'notes.license.can.h': '✅ What you can do',
    'notes.license.can.p': 'Use Noesis for any purpose (personal or commercial) · Copy the HTML file · Modify the code · Distribute with the copyright notice · All free, no registration required',
